  "lore": {
    "key": "Tbl_Unit_Desc_94",
    "english": "Taimanin, the 18th master of the Onigumo clan. The Onigumo clan is known to be a clan of Beast Art ninjas for generations, and its masters inherit the name 'Saburo'. The 18th Saburo, who succeeded the name as a girl, showed a rare talent as a child and was recognized as a master.\n\nThe 18th Saburo's Beast Art is a ninja art which is also called \"Beast Tamer\". It is a ninja art that controls a giant demonic spider named 'Daigoro'. The 18th Saburo, sitting on top and giving orders to Daigoro, which attacks the enemy ruthlessly with its rapid speed, teeth, venom, and web, is said to resemble the Arachne, a demonic beast of legend.",
    "japanese": "Taimanin, the 18th master of the Onigumo clan. The Onigumo clan is known to be a clan of Beast Art ninjas for generations, and its masters inherit the name 'Saburo'. The 18th Saburo, who succeeded the name as a girl, showed a rare talent as a child and was recognized as a master.\n\nThe 18th Saburo's Beast Art is a ninja art which is also called \"Beast Tamer\". It is a ninja art that controls a giant demonic spider named 'Daigoro'. The 18th Saburo, sitting on top and giving orders to Daigoro, which attacks the enemy ruthlessly with its rapid speed, teeth, venom, and web, is said to resemble the Arachne, a demonic beast of legend.",
    "korean": "Taimanin, the 18th master of the Onigumo clan. The Onigumo clan is known to be a clan of Beast Art ninjas for generations, and its masters inherit the name 'Saburo'. The 18th Saburo, who succeeded the name as a girl, showed a rare talent as a child and was recognized as a master.\n\nThe 18th Saburo's Beast Art is a ninja art which is also called \"Beast Tamer\". It is a ninja art that controls a giant demonic spider named 'Daigoro'. The 18th Saburo, sitting on top and giving orders to Daigoro, which attacks the enemy ruthlessly with its rapid speed, teeth, venom, and web, is said to resemble the Arachne, a demonic beast of legend.",
    "chinese_simplified": "Taimanin, the 18th master of the Onigumo clan. The Onigumo clan is known to be a clan of Beast Art ninjas for generations, and its masters inherit the name 'Saburo'. The 18th Saburo, who succeeded the name as a girl, showed a rare talent as a child and was recognized as a master.\n\nThe 18th Saburo's Beast Art is a ninja art which is also called \"Beast Tamer\". It is a ninja art that controls a giant demonic spider named 'Daigoro'. The 18th Saburo, sitting on top and giving orders to Daigoro, which attacks the enemy ruthlessly with its rapid speed, teeth, venom, and web, is said to resemble the Arachne, a demonic beast of legend.",
    "chinese_traditional": "Taimanin, the 18th master of the Onigumo clan. The Onigumo clan is known to be a clan of Beast Art ninjas for generations, and its masters inherit the name 'Saburo'. The 18th Saburo, who succeeded the name as a girl, showed a rare talent as a child and was recognized as a master.\n\nThe 18th Saburo's Beast Art is a ninja art which is also called \"Beast Tamer\". It is a ninja art that controls a giant demonic spider named 'Daigoro'. The 18th Saburo, sitting on top and giving orders to Daigoro, which attacks the enemy ruthlessly with its rapid speed, teeth, venom, and web, is said to resemble the Arachne, a demonic beast of legend.",
    "spanish": "Taimanin, the 18th master of the Onigumo clan. The Onigumo clan is known to be a clan of Beast Art ninjas for generations, and its masters inherit the name 'Saburo'. The 18th Saburo, who succeeded the name as a girl, showed a rare talent as a child and was recognized as a master.\n\nThe 18th Saburo's Beast Art is a ninja art which is also called \"Beast Tamer\". It is a ninja art that controls a giant demonic spider named 'Daigoro'. The 18th Saburo, sitting on top and giving orders to Daigoro, which attacks the enemy ruthlessly with its rapid speed, teeth, venom, and web, is said to resemble the Arachne, a demonic beast of legend."
